9
00:00:33.283 --> 00:00:36.495
When the author and theorist of ancient astronauts

10
00:00:36.662 --> 00:00:39.581
Erich von Däniken. author of *Chariots of the Gods*?

11
00:00:39.790 --> 00:00:43.126
he presented a revolutionary theory.

12
00:00:43.293 --> 00:00:45.671
He suggested that aliens

13
00:00:45.837 --> 00:00:48.340
not only did he come to Earth in the distant past.

14
00:00:48.549 --> 00:00:51.969
but that they left hidden messages for us to discover

15
00:00:52.135 --> 00:00:56.265
once we developed the right technology to decipher them.

16
00:00:56.431 --> 00:01:00.269
A convincing example are geoglyphs.

17
00:01:00.435 --> 00:01:03.897
massive shapes and figures carved into the landscape

18
00:01:04.105 --> 00:01:08.318
which are only fully visible from the sky.

19
00:01:11.780 --> 00:01:14.324
[Narrator] Saudi Arabia. 2004.

20
00:01:16.368 --> 00:01:20.163
While exploring the ancient lava fields of Harrat Khaybar.

21
00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:23.625
amateur archaeologist Dr. Abdullah Al-Saeed

22
00:01:23.792 --> 00:01:27.588
comes across a series of what appear to be stone walls.

23
00:01:27.754 --> 00:01:30.465
each about one meter high.

24
00:01:32.134 --> 00:01:35.429
From the ground level. Dr. Al-Saeed concludes

25
00:01:35.596 --> 00:01:38.515
that the structures do not have a clear pattern or purpose.

26
00:01:41.935 --> 00:01:44.855
I mean. only after four years.

27
00:01:45.022 --> 00:01:49.318
when he obtains satellite photos of the same area.

28
00:01:49.443 --> 00:01:52.654
What he sees amazes him.

29
00:01:52.821 --> 00:01:55.282
There. detectable from the sky.

30
00:01:55.449 --> 00:01:59.161
are a vast collection of over 400 stone enclosures.

31
00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:03.957
Known to the local Bedouins as "The Works of the Elders".

32
00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:07.002
These mysterious structures are being rapidly examined

33
00:02:07.169 --> 00:02:11.048
and it turns out they stretch for hundreds of kilometers.

34
00:02:12.049 --> 00:02:13.925
[Andrew Collins] They were in what's called...

35
00:02:14.092 --> 00:02:16.803
like a lava field of activity.

36
00:02:16.928 --> 00:02:18.472
And they are generally described

37
00:02:18.639 --> 00:02:20.515
be like a kite...

38
00:02:22.643 --> 00:02:24.436
...or as gates.

39
00:02:24.603 --> 00:02:28.815
which are more rectilinear forms of them.

40
00:02:30.692 --> 00:02:33.111
And there are literally hundreds of these.

41
00:02:33.278 --> 00:02:37.366
In fact. they extend all the way to Saudi Arabia.

42
00:02:37.532 --> 00:02:39.951
just across the Jordan

43
00:02:40.118 --> 00:02:41.912
and in Syria.

44
00:02:43.455 --> 00:02:45.540
[Hugh Newman] They're kind of like angular pyramids. almost...

45
00:02:45.749 --> 00:02:47.918
breaking apart in the distance like runways.

46
00:02:48.085 --> 00:02:50.295
widening at one end and being short at the other end.

47
00:02:51.505 --> 00:02:53.256
[Narrator] Although there is no record

48
00:02:53.423 --> 00:02:55.884
indicating when these structures were built.

49
00:02:56.051 --> 00:02:58.762
who built them or why

50
00:02:58.929 --> 00:03:02.474
the prevailing theory among mainstream archaeologists

51
00:03:02.641 --> 00:03:05.185
is that they were built for hunting purposes.

52
00:03:05.352 --> 00:03:07.646
many thousands of years ago.

53
00:03:08.730 --> 00:03:12.025
What we think are prehistoric hunting grounds.

54
00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:13.568
where gazelle and other animals

55
00:03:13.735 --> 00:03:15.362
would have pushed into the enclosure.

56
00:03:15.529 --> 00:03:18.990
and then. on the outside of the enclosure.

57
00:03:19.157 --> 00:03:21.410
Pits were dug. and animals fell into the pits.

58
00:03:23.078 --> 00:03:24.454
Kites. when you visit them on earth.

59
00:03:24.621 --> 00:03:26.123
they are very hard to find.

60
00:03:27.207 --> 00:03:29.084
In the air. you get the whole pattern.

61
00:03:29.251 --> 00:03:31.211
There are literally thousands of them.

62
00:03:31.378 --> 00:03:35.090
And they must have been used for thousands of years.

63
00:03:35.257 --> 00:03:36.883
And why did they fall into disuse?

64
00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:38.593
This is an answer I have not yet received.

65
00:03:39.886 --> 00:03:41.346
[Narrator] Although the theory that

66
00:03:41.513 --> 00:03:42.806
stone structures were used

67
00:03:42.973 --> 00:03:44.599
for hunting purposes it is convincing.

68
00:03:44.724 --> 00:03:47.477
Ancient astronaut theorists argue

69
00:03:47.644 --> 00:03:49.271
that if these structures were really used

70
00:03:49.438 --> 00:03:51.398
for hunting gazelles.

71
00:03:51.565 --> 00:03:54.276
the walls should have been over a meter high.

72
00:03:54.443 --> 00:03:58.405
since a gazelle can jump more than three meters in the air.

73
00:03:59.573 --> 00:04:01.283
Instead. they suggest

74
00:04:01.408 --> 00:04:04.786
because the structures are only visible from the air.

75
00:04:04.953 --> 00:04:07.164
should be considered geoglyphs.

76
00:04:08.290 --> 00:04:09.749
[Paul Bahn] A geoglyph is basically just...

77
00:04:09.916 --> 00:04:11.209
a landscape drawing.

78
00:04:11.376 --> 00:04:13.253
Usually on a fairly large scale.

79
00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:15.172
Most geoglyphs are found in deserts.

80
00:04:15.338 --> 00:04:16.923
and in the deserts you have a phenomenon

81
00:04:17.048 --> 00:04:18.675
which we call a desert lake.

82
00:04:18.841 --> 00:04:21.803
It's just a natural dark patina that builds up on the surface.

83
00:04:21.928 --> 00:04:24.765
And so. if you move the dark parts to one side.

84
00:04:24.931 --> 00:04:27.392
expose the lighter soil or sand underneath.

85
00:04:27.559 --> 00:04:30.187
this is one way to make a drawing.

86
00:04:30.353 --> 00:04:32.063
The second basic technique

87
00:04:32.230 --> 00:04:34.149
is to use the dark stones

88
00:04:34.316 --> 00:04:36.610
and gather them together to form shapes.

89
00:04:36.777 --> 00:04:41.072
geometric shapes. animal shapes or anything else.

90
00:04:41.239 --> 00:04:42.449
And the third basic technique

91
00:04:42.616 --> 00:04:44.367
it is simply a combination of the two.

92
00:04:44.534 --> 00:04:46.661
Move things aside to expose the brightness.

93
00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:48.747
You use the dark stones to create patterns.

94
00:04:48.914 --> 00:04:50.916
So you get a very nice combination between the two.

95
00:04:51.958 --> 00:04:53.335
In recent years. thanks to modern technology.

96
00:04:53.502 --> 00:04:55.837
and especially satellite photos.

97
00:04:56.004 --> 00:04:58.298
there has been an explosion of new discoveries

98
00:04:58.507 --> 00:05:00.717
from geoglyphs that I didn't know about before.

99
00:05:03.053 --> 00:05:05.639
[Collins] The interesting fact about all of this

100
00:05:05.764 --> 00:05:08.725
is that they point to heaven.

101
00:05:08.892 --> 00:05:11.228
And what could that tell us?

102
00:05:11.394 --> 00:05:14.940
Well. the first thing is that many of the geoglyphs

103
00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:18.693
that we know today were only discovered

104
00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:23.406
once aerial studies began around the 1920s.

105
00:05:23.573 --> 00:05:26.117
All was truly revealed only

106
00:05:26.284 --> 00:05:28.870
once the aircraft took off.

107
00:05:29.037 --> 00:05:31.748
And that tells us something very. very important.

108
00:05:33.708 --> 00:05:36.878
Most geoglyphs only make sense when seen from above.

109
00:05:37.045 --> 00:05:39.965
Therefore. it seems that these are messages

110
00:05:40.131 --> 00:05:42.717
towards something non-human. something up there.

111
00:05:43.927 --> 00:05:45.220
[Narrator] When now the legendary Nazca Lines

112
00:05:45.428 --> 00:05:49.349
from Peru were first discovered in 1927.

113
00:05:49.516 --> 00:05:52.143
were considered a unique phenomenon.

114
00:05:52.310 --> 00:05:55.814
But now. with the advantage of satellite imagery.

115
00:05:55.981 --> 00:05:58.149
Thousands of ancient geoglyphs are discovered

116
00:05:58.316 --> 00:06:00.110
all around the world:

117
00:06:00.277 --> 00:06:02.612
in Kazakhstan.

118
00:06:02.779 --> 00:06:05.323
in the southwestern United States.

119
00:06:05.448 --> 00:06:07.534
in the Atacama Desert of Chile

120
00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:09.828
and in Bolivia.

121
00:06:11.204 --> 00:06:13.039
[Collins] Almost everywhere in the world.

122
00:06:13.164 --> 00:06:15.917
we find what are known as geoglyphs.

123
00:06:16.084 --> 00:06:19.129
whether it's the Nazca Lines in Peru.

124
00:06:19.296 --> 00:06:21.548
British geoglyphs.

125
00:06:21.715 --> 00:06:24.050
those from the Middle East.

126
00:06:24.217 --> 00:06:26.761
they are practically universal

127
00:06:26.928 --> 00:06:28.763
all around the world.

128
00:06:28.889 --> 00:06:31.766
and have been appearing for many hundreds of years.

129
00:06:32.809 --> 00:06:34.561
[Narrator] But why would ancient people

130
00:06:34.686 --> 00:06:37.522
in so many different places around the world

131
00:06:37.647 --> 00:06:41.985
Are they all making signs that can only be seen from above?

132
00:06:42.152 --> 00:06:43.820
We don't know for sure what

133
00:06:44.029 --> 00:06:45.655
Ancient peoples tried to communicate through geoglyphs.

134
00:06:45.864 --> 00:06:48.074
but the most important thing is

135
00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:51.161
the time and effort put into building them.

136
00:06:51.286 --> 00:06:52.996
These are not quick sketches.

137
00:06:53.163 --> 00:06:55.290
Many of them are projects of the entire community.

138
00:06:55.457 --> 00:06:58.043
And the time you spend working on them

139
00:06:58.168 --> 00:07:00.337
is the time not spent gathering food.

140
00:07:00.545 --> 00:07:02.505
not spent defending your land.

141
00:07:02.672 --> 00:07:05.800
That's time not spent taking care of your children.

142
00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:08.678
So. the first thing they communicate

143
00:07:08.845 --> 00:07:10.513
it is for the community itself.

144
00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:12.265
what is important to the community.

145
00:07:13.558 --> 00:07:14.893
[Narrator] But there could be another one.

146
00:07:15.060 --> 00:07:17.562
an even more incredible explanation?

147
00:07:17.729 --> 00:07:20.774
It is possible that these ancient geoglyphs

148
00:07:20.940 --> 00:07:23.985
were created not for a terrestrial purpose

149
00:07:24.152 --> 00:07:26.571
but for an alien?

150
00:07:27.614 --> 00:07:30.492
Ancient astronaut theorists say yes.

151
00:07:30.659 --> 00:07:32.869
and suggests that additional clues may be found

152
00:07:33.036 --> 00:07:35.163
by examining similar shapes and symbols

153
00:07:35.288 --> 00:07:37.832
which are produced on a much smaller scale.

154
00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:42.879
Geoglyphs are giant versions of

155
00:07:43.004 --> 00:07:44.714
what we know as petroglyphs.

156
00:07:44.881 --> 00:07:47.425
the most obvious being the cave art we would see

157
00:07:47.592 --> 00:07:50.804
on rock surfaces around the world

158
00:07:50.970 --> 00:07:53.807
which dates back many. many thousands of years.

159
00:07:53.973 --> 00:07:56.267
Petroglyphs are images carved into rocks.

160
00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:59.020
or incised or hammered.

161
00:07:59.229 --> 00:08:01.564
They appear all over the world.

162
00:08:01.731 --> 00:08:03.775
from Australia to Asia.

163
00:08:03.942 --> 00:08:06.444
Europe. Africa. through the Americas.

164
00:08:09.823 --> 00:08:11.116
[Narrator] Maybe more interesting

165
00:08:11.282 --> 00:08:12.867
than the petroglyphs themselves

166
00:08:13.034 --> 00:08:15.370
are the strange similarities between them

167
00:08:15.537 --> 00:08:17.706
and their geoglyphic brethren.

168
00:08:17.872 --> 00:08:21.418
We see certain symbols appearing over and over again.

169
00:08:22.544 --> 00:08:25.171
There are many geometric shapes.

170
00:08:25.338 --> 00:08:28.633
They take the form of spirals.

171
00:08:28.800 --> 00:08:30.719
of concentric rings.

172
00:08:30.844 --> 00:08:34.972
and other more rectilinear or abstract designs.

173
00:08:35.140 --> 00:08:37.015
I am something that is practical.

174
00:08:37.225 --> 00:08:39.352
universal throughout the world.

175
00:08:39.519 --> 00:08:41.145
One of the most interesting geoglyphs

176
00:08:41.312 --> 00:08:43.940
that you have at Nazca is the geoglyph of the Sun. Star. Cross.

177
00:08:44.149 --> 00:08:46.401
which is really very complicated.

178
00:08:46.526 --> 00:08:51.489
a huge mandala of interconnected stars and triangles.

179
00:08:51.656 --> 00:08:53.867
And it's something we see all over the world.

180
00:08:54.034 --> 00:08:57.620
and in Tibet and India in the form of mandalas and even yantras.

181
00:08:57.829 --> 00:08:59.205
So. things like this.

182
00:08:59.372 --> 00:09:02.667
which are so geometrically complicated

183
00:09:02.834 --> 00:09:04.377
and are found all over the world.

184
00:09:04.586 --> 00:09:06.171
indicates that there was some kind of

185
00:09:06.337 --> 00:09:09.591
world symbolic language

186
00:09:09.758 --> 00:09:13.344
which was brought here by a superior intelligence.

187
00:09:13.511 --> 00:09:15.388
probably aliens.

188
00:09:19.350 --> 00:09:20.894
In 2005. an unusual feature

189
00:09:21.061 --> 00:09:23.271
was discovered in central Canada

190
00:09:23.438 --> 00:09:26.566
which some believe contains the best evidence yet

191
00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:30.528
a hidden message left by extraterrestrial visitors.

192
00:09:30.695 --> 00:09:34.574
It is a colossal geoglyph that has become known

193
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:37.202
as the Guardian of the Badlands.

194
00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:44.959
[Narrator] Gravelbourg. Saskatchewan.

195
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:47.378
2005.

196
00:09:48.463 --> 00:09:51.299
Grandma Lynn Hickox. 53 years old

197
00:09:51.508 --> 00:09:54.511
scan GPS directions to a local museum

198
00:09:54.677 --> 00:09:57.889
on the satellite when something catches his attention:

199
00:09:58.973 --> 00:10:01.726
a geographical feature that bears a striking resemblance

200
00:10:01.893 --> 00:10:03.770
to a human face.

201
00:10:04.896 --> 00:10:07.357
It looks so much like a man-made structure

202
00:10:07.524 --> 00:10:09.818
that she posts the image on a forum.

203
00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:14.364
Almost overnight. the image went viral.

204
00:10:14.531 --> 00:10:16.533
and becomes known everywhere

205
00:10:16.699 --> 00:10:19.202
as "Guardian of the Badlands".

206
00:10:20.745 --> 00:10:22.080
It's quite striking.

207
00:10:22.205 --> 00:10:23.873
It's clearly a face.

208
00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:26.459
The forehead. nose. lips. chin are well formed.

209
00:10:26.668 --> 00:10:29.170
The hairstyle. a little less.

210
00:10:29.337 --> 00:10:31.881
but they could clearly be seen as feathers.

211
00:10:32.006 --> 00:10:34.134
The Badlands Guardian appears to be

212
00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:37.387
a giant geoglyph near Alberta. Canada.

213
00:10:37.554 --> 00:10:40.890
And to see this from Google Earth or satellite imagery.

214
00:10:41.057 --> 00:10:44.894
you would think it was created by humans many. many years ago.

215
00:10:45.061 --> 00:10:48.189
[William Saunders] Badlands Guardian is a flop.

216
00:10:48.356 --> 00:10:51.276
or a head and shoulders presentation.

217
00:10:51.442 --> 00:10:54.112
of an indigenous male person.

218
00:10:54.279 --> 00:10:57.073
It is so striking because it is

219
00:10:57.240 --> 00:10:59.242
the indigenous population of the area.

220
00:10:59.367 --> 00:11:02.036
He doesn't look like a Scotsman wearing a kilt.

221
00:11:02.203 --> 00:11:04.330
he doesn't look like an African warrior.

222
00:11:04.497 --> 00:11:08.793
He appears to be an indigenous. uh. native to the area.

223
00:11:09.961 --> 00:11:12.505
[Narrator] It is possible that the resemblance of a human face

224
00:11:12.672 --> 00:11:14.924
formed naturally in the ground?

225
00:11:15.091 --> 00:11:18.094
Many of those who reviewed Badlands Guardian

226
00:11:18.261 --> 00:11:21.514
suggests that. based on the amount of detail it displays.

227
00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:23.600
this is very unlikely.

228
00:11:25.185 --> 00:11:27.353
When the mainstream scientific community looks

229
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:28.938
to the Badlands Guardian.

230
00:11:29.147 --> 00:11:30.857
their first explanation is that

231
00:11:31.065 --> 00:11:33.693
it was created by weathering. rain and water leaks.

232
00:11:33.860 --> 00:11:35.737
But there are so many details

233
00:11:35.945 --> 00:11:37.614
that we see in this formation

234
00:11:37.780 --> 00:11:40.033
that it far surpasses anything nature could create.

235
00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:42.827
It doesn't just have basic facial features.

236
00:11:42.994 --> 00:11:45.413
has secondary facial features. such as eyelids.

237
00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:46.915
The only thing missing from

238
00:11:47.081 --> 00:11:48.833
The Badlands Guardian is an ear feature.

239
00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:51.544
Now. the interesting thing is that.

240
00:11:51.711 --> 00:11:53.046
local government in Canada.

241
00:11:53.213 --> 00:11:54.923
they had found a gas deposit there.

242
00:11:55.089 --> 00:11:56.716
Exactly where the ear should be.

243
00:11:56.883 --> 00:11:58.468
There might have been an ear there at one time.

244
00:11:58.635 --> 00:12:00.345
but now. because they put an access road there

245
00:12:00.511 --> 00:12:03.348
and they built this gas plant. which was completely wiped out.

246
00:12:03.514 --> 00:12:07.435
Archaeologists are often wrong about ancient sites.

247
00:12:07.602 --> 00:12:10.521
And what actually is a pyramid?

248
00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:13.775
which is now. let's say. covered with earth

249
00:12:13.942 --> 00:12:16.402
and it has a forest on it

250
00:12:16.527 --> 00:12:18.988
it can be mistaken for a simple natural hill.

251
00:12:19.155 --> 00:12:23.660
This happened in... South America. in China.

252
00:12:23.868 --> 00:12:26.120
Archaeologists are constantly

253
00:12:26.246 --> 00:12:28.414
discovering that the things they consider natural

254
00:12:28.581 --> 00:12:30.708
are actually artificial.

255
00:12:32.126 --> 00:12:34.003
[Narrator] Some of the geoglyphs found

256
00:12:34.170 --> 00:12:35.880
from all over the world have formed

257
00:12:36.005 --> 00:12:38.591
simply by removing the top layer of soil

258
00:12:38.758 --> 00:12:41.469
to expose the lighter colored dirt underneath.

259
00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:45.473
But if the Badlands Guardian is also a geoglyph.

260
00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:48.309
creating it would have been an enormous undertaking.

261
00:12:49.310 --> 00:12:52.105
Massive. concave formation

262
00:12:52.272 --> 00:12:54.107
it's almost half a mile long.

263
00:12:54.274 --> 00:12:57.610
and is over 330 meters wide.

264
00:12:58.820 --> 00:13:01.614
For comparison. Mount Rushmore National Monument

265
00:13:01.781 --> 00:13:05.994
in South Dakota. which was completed in 1941.

266
00:13:06.160 --> 00:13:10.164
it is about 80 feet high and 200 feet wide.

